South Africans have always known the country’s health system is not all it’s cracked up to be. No amount of government spin can hide the fact the country’s health system is itself sick: a shortage of doctors and medicines and poor management or gross negligence characterise the system. So when the coronavirus (Covid-19) started making its way out of Wuhan city in China to multiple destinations around the world, only the most ignorant optimists believed South Africa was ready to effectively deal with it, and it didn’t take long for the government’s promises of “all is under control” to be...